[[{{PAGENAME}}]] is a regional [[Sōja (Shinto)|Sōja shrine]]. It enshrines many kami of the local region.<!-- Content taken from [[Sōja (Shinto)]] explaining the concept of it -->

It contrasts with provincial Soja shrines which enshrine all the kami of a province<ref>https://archive.ph/wip/XtZfZ</ref>


Here is a list of provincial soja including this one

* {{ill|Akasaka Uenoyama Shrine|ja|赤坂上之山神社}} 
* {{ill|Unakoro Waki Shrine|ja|宇奈己呂和気神社}} 
* {{ill|Ono Shrine (Ritto City)|ja|大野神社 (栗東市)}} 
* {{ill|Ogami Shrine (Tonami City)|ja|雄神神社 (砺波市)}} 
* {{ill|Kainan Shrine|ja|海南神社}} 
* {{ill|Katsushika Shrine|ja|葛飾神社}} 
* {{ill|Katsube Shrine|ja|勝部神社}} 
* {{ill|Mukuhashi Shrine|ja|椋橋総社}} 
* {{ill|Kotai Jingu (Fujisawa City)|ja|皇大神宮 (藤沢市)}} 
* {{ill|Gosho Shrine (Sammu City)|ja|五所神社 (山武市)}} 
* {{ill|Sakata Shinmei Shrine|ja|坂田神明宮}} 
* {{ill|Shinkai Sansha Shrine|ja|新海三社神社}} 
* {{ill|Sazama Shrine (Daito City)|ja|坐摩神社 (大東市)}} 
* {{ill|Kenda Suga Shrine|ja|健田須賀神社}} 
* {{ill|Tachibana Shrine (Kawasaki City)|ja|橘樹神社 (川崎市)}} 
* {{ill|Torakashi Shrine|ja|虎柏神社}} 
* {{ill|Nagao Shrine|ja|長尾神社}} 
* {{ill|Nanba Shrine|ja|難波神社|de|Namba-Schrein|fr|Namba-jinja|simple}} (may have historically been a provincal one)
* {{ill|Arayaza Amaterasu Mitama Shrine|ja|新屋坐天照御魂神社}}
* {{ill|Nogi Shrine (Tokyo)|lt=Nogi Shrine|ja|能義神社}}
* {{ill|Hotaka Shrine|ja|穂高神社|simple}}
* {{ill|Washinomiya Shrine|ja|鷲宮神社}}


