'''Zama Shrine''' (坐摩神社) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|de|Shintō-Schrein|ja|神社|zh|神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinto shrine|qq=}} located in Hiranoya, {{ill|Daitō City|de|Daitō|ja|大東市|zh|大东市|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Daitō City|qq=}}, {{ill|Osaka Prefecture|de|Präfektur Osaka|ja|大阪府|zh|大阪府|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Osaka Prefecture|qq=}}.

<br />
[[Sazama Shrine (Daito City)]] is a regional [[Sōja (Shinto)|Sōja shrine]]. It enshrines many kami of the local region.

It contrasts with provincial Soja shrines which enshrine all the kami of a province<ref>https://archive.ph/wip/XtZfZ</ref>

It is related to [[Ikasuri Shrine]]

